zimaos-tailscale-sysext
=======================

Build scripts and packaging in this repository are licensed under the MIT
License (see LICENSE).

Bundled / referenced upstream components:

  Tailscale (https://github.com/tailscale/tailscale)
    Licensed under BSD-3-Clause. The build script downloads the official
    static Linux release tarball from https://pkgs.tailscale.com/stable/
    and bundles the `tailscale` and `tailscaled` binaries into the
    sysext image. No source modification is performed.

  systemd unit file (systemd/tailscaled.service)
    Adapted from the upstream tailscale.com cmd/tailscaled/tailscaled.service
    (BSD-3-Clause). Modifications:
      - StateDirectory replaced by an explicit --state path under /DATA/
        (ZimaOS-specific — /var/lib/ is tmpfs on this OS).
      - EnvironmentFile made optional (prefixed with `-`).
      - Defaults inlined via Environment= so /etc/default/tailscaled is
        not required.

Inspired by the Buildroot `package/tailscale/tailscale.mk` recipe
(https://github.com/buildroot/buildroot/blob/master/package/tailscale/tailscale.mk).
The install layout mirrors the buildroot package one-to-one; the difference
is that this repo distributes a runtime sysext extension instead of patching
the OS image itself, since the ZimaOS source tree is not public.
